  <section style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
    <h2 id="what-is-trap" style="font-size: 32px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-top: 48px;">What Is Trap Music?</h2>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 24px;">Trap music originated in Atlanta in the early 2000s and has become one of the most dominant genres in hip-hop and pop. Characterized by rolling hi-hats, heavy 808 bass, crisp snares, and dark atmospheric melodies, trap has influenced everything from mainstream rap to EDM.</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 24px;">Key Characteristics of Trap Beats:</p>
    <ul style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding-left: 24px;">
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;"><strong>Tempo:</strong> Typically 130-160 BPM (most commonly 140 BPM)</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;"><strong>808 Bass:</strong> Deep, sustained bass notes that define the low end</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;"><strong>Hi-Hats:</strong> Rapid, rolling hi-hat patterns (often triplets or 32nd notes)</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;"><strong>Snares:</strong> Layered, snappy snares on beat 3</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;"><strong>Melody:</strong> Dark, atmospheric sounds (piano, strings, synths)</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
    <h2 id="step1" style="font-size: 32px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-top: 48px;">Step 1: Set Your Tempo and Key</h2>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 24px;">Before you start, establish your foundation:</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 16px;"><strong>Tempo:</strong> Set your DAW to 140 BPM for classic trap, or experiment between 130-160 BPM. Slower tempos (130-140) give a heavier feel, while faster (150-160) adds energy.</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 24px;"><strong>Key:</strong> Trap often uses minor keys for dark vibes. Popular choices: A minor, D minor, F# minor, C minor. Choose a key and stick to it for melodic elements.</p>
  </section>

  <section style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
    <h2 id="step2" style="font-size: 32px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-top: 48px;">Step 2: Create the 808 Bass Pattern</h2>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 24px;">The 808 is the heart of trap music. Here's how to make it slap:</p>
    <h3 style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 16px; margin-top: 32px;">Choosing Your 808</h3>
    <ul style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding-left: 24px;">
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Use a long, sustained 808 sample</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Classic choices: Roland TR-808 bass drum, Spinz 808, Zay 808</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Ensure it's tuned (most 808s are tuned to C)</li>
    </ul>
    <h3 style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 16px; margin-top: 32px;">808 Pattern Tips</h3>
    <ul style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding-left: 24px;">
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;"><strong>Root Notes:</strong> Place 808s on strong beats (1 and 3) or offbeats</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;"><strong>Slides:</strong> Use pitch glides between notes for movement</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;"><strong>Variation:</strong> Change patterns every 4-8 bars to keep interest</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;"><strong>Length:</strong> Adjust note length to control bounce (shorter = bouncier)</li>
    </ul>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 24px;"><strong>Pro Tip:</strong> Make sure your 808 is in key with your melody. Out-of-tune 808s are the #1 beginner mistake.</p>
  </section>

  <section style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
    <h2 id="step3" style="font-size: 32px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-top: 48px;">Step 3: Program Trap Hi-Hats</h2>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 24px;">Rolling hi-hats are the signature of trap. Here's how to create them:</p>
    <h3 style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 16px; margin-top: 32px;">Basic Hi-Hat Pattern</h3>
    <ul style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding-left: 24px;">
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Start with 8th or 16th note hi-hats on every beat</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Add triplet rolls (3 notes per beat) for movement</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Use 32nd notes sparingly for intense rolls</li>
    </ul>
    <h3 style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 16px; margin-top: 32px;">Velocity Variation</h3>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 24px;">Vary the velocity (volume) of hi-hat hits to create groove. Generally: strong hits on downbeats, softer on offbeats and rolls.</p>
    <h3 style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 16px; margin-top: 32px;">Layering Hi-Hats</h3>
    <ul style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding-left: 24px;">
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Use 2-3 different hi-hat samples for variety</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Pan some left/right for width</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Add open hats occasionally for accent</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
    <h2 id="step4" style="font-size: 32px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-top: 48px;">Step 4: Add Snares and Claps</h2>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 24px;">Snares typically hit on beat 3 (the "3" in a 4/4 bar). Here's how to make them punch:</p>
    <ul style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding-left: 24px;">
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;"><strong>Layering:</strong> Use 2-3 snare/clap samples layered together</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;"><strong>Tuning:</strong> Pitch snares down slightly for weight</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;"><strong>Reverb:</strong> Add a short reverb (0.5-1.0s) for space</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;"><strong>Variation:</strong> Add ghost notes (softer hits) between main snares</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
    <h2 id="step5" style="font-size: 32px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-top: 48px;">Step 5: Create a Dark Melody</h2>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 24px;">Trap melodies are atmospheric and dark. Common instruments:</p>
    <ul style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding-left: 24px;">
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Piano (most popular)</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Strings (violins, cellos)</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Bells and mallets</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Synth pads</li>
    </ul>
    <h3 style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 16px; margin-top: 32px;">Melody Writing Tips</h3>
    <ul style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding-left: 24px;">
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Stick to your minor scale</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Use repeating patterns (4-8 note loops)</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Add space - Trap melodies are often sparse</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Layer multiple instruments for fullness</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
    <h2 id="mixing" style="font-size: 32px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-top: 48px;">Mixing Your Trap Beat</h2>
    <h3 style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 16px; margin-top: 32px;">808 Bass</h3>
    <ul style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding-left: 24px;">
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Boost around 50-80 Hz for power</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Add soft clipping or distortion for punch</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Sidechain to kick for clarity</li>
    </ul>
    <h3 style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 16px; margin-top: 32px;">Hi-Hats</h3>
    <ul style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding-left: 24px;">
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;">High-pass filter below 8-10 kHz</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Add slight reverb for space</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Pan for stereo width</li>
    </ul>
    <h3 style="font-size: 24px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 16px; margin-top: 32px;">Melody</h3>
    <ul style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding-left: 24px;">
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;">EQ out muddy frequencies (200-500 Hz)</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Add reverb for atmosphere</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;">Compress gently for consistency</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

