  <section style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
    <h2 id="mistakes" style="font-size: 32px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 24px; margin-top: 48px;">Common Trap Beat Mistakes to Avoid</h2>
    <ul style="margin-bottom: 24px; padding-left: 24px;">
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;"><strong>Out-of-Tune 808s:</strong> Always tune your 808 to your melody's key</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;"><strong>Too Many Elements:</strong> Trap is about space and impact, not density</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;"><strong>Weak Snares:</strong> Layer and process your snares properly</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;"><strong>Boring Hi-Hats:</strong> Add rolls and variation, don't just loop the same pattern</li>
      <li style="margin-bottom: 12px;"><strong>Muddy Mix:</strong> EQ properly and give each element its own space</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

